.TH "binder_update_ref_for_handle" 9 "binder_update_ref_for_handle" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
binder_update_ref_for_handle \- inc/dec the ref for given handle
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" binder_update_ref_for_handle
.BI "(struct binder_proc *proc "  ","
.BI "uint32_t desc "  ","
.BI "bool increment "  ","
.BI "bool strong "  ","
.BI "struct binder_ref_data *rdata "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "proc" 12
proc containing the ref
.IP "desc" 12
the handle associated with the ref
.IP "increment" 12
true=inc reference, false=dec reference
.IP "strong" 12
true=strong reference, false=weak reference
.IP "rdata" 12
the id/refcount data for the ref
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Given a proc and ref handle, increment or decrement the ref
according to "increment" arg.
.SH "RETURN"
0 if successful, else errno
